Class Rule

  • java.lang.Object
    • classes.Rule
  • public class Rule
extends java.lang.Object
    Date: Dec 12, 2019 This is a class that receives a Rule, with thresholds and a mode (being it Feature Envy or Long Method), and creates and runs a new RuleChecker accordingly.

        public Rule​(java.lang.String name,
            int Limit1,
            int Limit2,
            LogicParser lp,
            int mode)
     throws java.lang.Exception
        This Constructor creates a rule, and does it with the Rule.featureEnvy or Rule.longMethod in the mode parameter.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the Rule, for user recognition.
        Limit1 - The value of the first limit.
        Limit2 - The value of the second limit.
        lp - The selected logic comparison between the two thresholds
        mode - The selected of the rule.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - If the mode isn't recognized, the constructor will throw an exception.

        public boolean runRule​(int param1,
                       int param2)
